  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nHooks cannot be used with JSPM build of React.\r\n\r\nFor this example:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n  <head>\r\n    <title>Untitled App</title>\r\n  </head>\r\n  <body>\r\n    <div id=\"root\"></div>\r\n    <script type=\"module\">\r\n      import React from 'https://dev.jspm.io/react@16.7.0-alpha.0'\r\n      import ReactDOM from 'https://dev.jspm.io/react-dom@16.7.0-alpha.0'\r\n\r\n      function Button(props) {\r\n        const [position, setPosition] = React.useState({});\r\n\r\n        return React.createElement('button', {\r\n          children: props.children,\r\n          onMouseMove: event => {\r\n            setPosition({\r\n              left: event.clientX + 2,\r\n              top: event.clientY + 2\r\n            })\r\n          },\r\n          style: {\r\n            ...position,\r\n            position: position.left ? 'fixed' : 'absolute',\r\n          }\r\n        })\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      ReactDOM.render(\r\n        React.createElement(Button, null, \"Add a contact\"),\r\n        document.getElementById('root')\r\n      )\r\n    </script>\r\n  </body>\r\n</html>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe following error is given: \r\n\r\n```\r\nUncaught Error: Hooks can only be called inside the body of a function component.\r\n    at invariant (react.development.dew.js:100)\r\n    at resolveDispatcher (react.development.dew.js:1475)\r\n    at Object.useState (react.development.dew.js:1498)\r\n    at Button (index.html:15)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, the same code works fine when loading React via an unpkg `<script>` tag.\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n  <head>\r\n    <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/react@16.7.0-alpha.0/umd/react.development.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/react-dom@16.7.0-alpha.0/umd/react-dom.development.js\"></script>\r\n    <title>Untitled App</title>\r\n  </head>\r\n  <body>\r\n    <div id=\"root\"></div>\r\n    <script type=\"module\">\r\n      function Button(props) {\r\n        const [position, setPosition] = React.useState({});\r\n\r\n        return React.createElement('button', {\r\n          children: props.children,\r\n          onMouseMove: event => {\r\n            setPosition({\r\n              left: event.clientX + 2,\r\n              top: event.clientY + 2\r\n            })\r\n          },\r\n          style: {\r\n            ...position,\r\n            position: position.left ? 'fixed' : 'absolute',\r\n          }\r\n        })\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      ReactDOM.render(\r\n        React.createElement(Button, null, \"Add a contact\"),\r\n        document.getElementById('root')\r\n      )\r\n    </script>\r\n  </body>\r\n</html>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce and if possible a minimal demo of the problem. Your bug will get fixed much faster if we can run your code and it doesn't have dependencies other than React. Paste the link to your JSFiddle (https://jsfiddle.net/Luktwrdm/) or CodeSandbox (https://codesandbox.io/s/new) example below:**\r\n\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/qu5dh2ca/1/\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nJSPM and UNPKG should behave identically.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n16.7.0-alpha.0, development mode bundle.",
